+        # Note: this used to also add 2D physical groups here for each BC/load
+        # surface, indexed positionally (surfaces[i]) rather than by actual
+        # geometric location, and named after the planner's free-text
+        # "location" string. Nothing downstream ever read those groups by
+        # name -- generate_input_deck() hardcodes NFIX/NLOAD literally -- and
+        # gmsh's Abaqus/CalculiX .inp writer exports any grouped surface as
+        # CPS6 (plane-stress) elements, which CalculiX then rejects outright
+        # for a 3D solid ("should lie in the z=0 plane"). NFIX/NLOAD are now
+        # identified directly by geometry and written as *NSET blocks in
+        # _write_bc_load_nsets(), so no 2D physical groups are needed at all;
+        # leaving surfaces ungrouped keeps gmsh from emitting them as elements.
